@startuml Memory Forensics - System Architecture (Simplified)

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

title Memory Forensics Automation Tool - System Architecture (Simplified)

' ==================== COMPONENTS ====================

component "Flutter\nDesktop UI" as UI #2196F3
component "Flask\nBackend API" as API #FF9800
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB #9C27B0
storage "File System\n(Memory Dumps)" as FS #9C27B0
queue "Redis\nJob Queue" as Redis #9C27B0
component "RQ Worker\n(Background)" as Worker #4CAF50
component "Volatility3\nCLI" as Vol3 #4CAF50

' ==================== RELATIONSHIPS ====================

UI -down-> API : "HTTP REST API"

API -down-> FS : "1. Store File"
API -down-> DB : "2. Save Metadata"
API -down-> Redis : "3. Enqueue Job"

Redis -down-> Worker : "4. Poll Jobs"

Worker -up-> DB : "Read Path &\nUpdate Status"
Worker -left-> FS : "Read Dump"
Worker -down-> Vol3 : "5. Execute Analysis"

Vol3 -up-> FS : "Save Report"

' ==================== NOTES ====================

note right of UI
  **Client**
  Desktop application
  (Windows/macOS/Linux)
end note

note right of API
  **REST API**
  File upload
  Case management
  Report retrieval
end note

note bottom of DB
  **Metadata**
  Cases & Files
  Status tracking
end note

note bottom of FS
  **Binary Storage**
  Memory dumps
  JSON reports
end note

note bottom of Redis
  **Async Queue**
  Job management
  (case_id only)
end note

note right of Worker
  **Background**
  Async processing
  SimpleWorker
end note

note right of Vol3
  **Analysis**
  Memory forensics
  Plugin execution
end note

@enduml
